In [21]:
import numpy as np
def plot_tree(model):
    n_features = X.shape[1]
    plt.rcParams["figure.figsize"]=(16,9)
    plt.barh(range(n_features), model.feature_importances_,
    align='center')
    plt.yticks(np.arange(n_features), train_cols)
    plt.xlabel(" ")
    plt.ylabel("")
    plt.ylim(-1, n_features)
plot_tree(tree)

#knn
from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier
import numpy as np
train_rate = []
test_rate = []
#      k  .
# k          
# 1  10  n_neighbors  
neighbors = range(1, 11)
for n in neighbors:
    #  
    knn = KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors=n)
    knn.fit(X_train_scaled, y_train)
    #   
    train_rate.append(knn.score(X_train_scaled, y_train))
    #   
    test_rate.append(knn.score(X_test_scaled, y_test))
test_arr=np.array(test_rate) #  
max_rate=np.max(test_arr) #  
idx=np.where(test_arr == max_rate)[0][0] #   
print(" k:",neighbors[idx])
print(" :",test_rate[idx])
